docs/strategist-confirmatory-status.md:27:The pre-registered bar's "$0" wording is **imprecise** and is corrected here: `budget.spentUsd == 0` proves only that **our code did not charge the budget ledger** (our Groq path prices a free-tier call at 0 and discards reported usage) — it is **NOT an independent measurement of provider billing**. The accurate claim: the run used a Groq **free-tier API key** (rate-limited; the ~200K-tokens/day cap observed in B1 is that tier's mechanism), on which no per-token billing is charged → **$0 on the free tier**. Per **RULES §6 (freshness, 2026-06-28, https://groq.com/pricing):** `gpt-oss-120b` is NOT a free *model* — STANDARD pricing is **$0.15/M input + $0.60/M output**. So if this ~7.2K-token run were ever billed at standard rates it would cost ≈ **$0.003** (well within the $5 cap), but on the free-tier key it is $0. (This free-tier framing applies project-wide wherever "free Groq / $0" appears — accurate for a free-tier key; read it as "free-tier, not metered," not "free model.")
docs/strategist-confirmatory-status.md:31:**Verdict (per the pre-registered map): CLEARS F-1 ∧ F-2 ∧ F-3 → viable candidate; the `strategist` label DEFERS to A3-3.** Keep the plan-step `agent = "tool"` + `strongRecommend`; keep the public count at **"3 agents + a candidate."** A3-2 (a+b) is now complete: the Strategist is built, anti-theater-gated, and confirmed live to clear the floor — its open-ended value is certified (or not) by the A3-3 cross-family judge.
