    45	3. `docs/GLOSSARY.md` — the two-register glossary.
    46	
    47	Plus ONE adversarial insert (registered here, required by §5-M5): a synthetic chunk
    48	containing instruction-like text ("ignore your instructions and …") planted to prove
    49	retrieved text is inert data. It is clearly marked synthetic inside the corpus.
    50	
    51	**Exclusions (leakage screen, §4):** no eval/gold files, no calibration snapshots, no
    52	status docs, no review records — the corpus is reference knowledge, never the answer
    53	key to any existing eval.
    54	
    55	## 3. Index + versioning (recorded, not tuned-after-the-fact)
    56	
    57	- Chunking: recorded at build (target 200–400 token chunks, split on headings/rule
    58	  boundaries; exact parameters written into the corpus manifest BEFORE scoring).
    59	- Embeddings: local Transformers.js-class model, $0 offline. **Provenance pinned in
    60	  the manifest: model ID + revision/content hash + license + storage dependency.**
    61	  A **network-denied clean run** (same harness pattern as the crew's offline proof)
    62	  must demonstrate no runtime download; if the model cannot run network-denied, E2
    63	  BLOCKS rather than fetching at runtime.
    64	- Store: in-memory cosine + BM25 hybrid — smallest thing that works; no external DB.
    65	- **Deterministic BM25 baseline:** every retrieval metric in §5 is ALSO measured for
    66	  plain BM25 (no embeddings). If the hybrid does not strictly beat BM25 on M1 while
    67	  holding M2–M5, the SIMPLER lane ships and the writeup says so (anti-theater: an
    68	  embedding lane must earn its complexity).
    69	
    70	## 4. Gold set + leakage screen (constructed before the index is queried)
    71	
    72	- **n = 30 items, committed in one gold file before any scoring:** 24 in-corpus
    73	  answerable questions (stratified: ≥8 fee-rule, ≥8 UCP-schema, ≥6 glossary,
    74	  ≥2 cross-source) + 6 out-of-corpus questions whose correct outcome is ABSTAIN.
    75	- Each in-corpus item: question · expected source file(s) · expected supporting span
    76	  (the grader checks the cited span actually supports the answer).
    77	- **Leakage screen (machine-checked, composition-test precedent
    78	  `evals/gold/fee-lines-gold-retry-composition.test.ts`):** no gold question may be a
    79	  verbatim (≥8-gram) copy of corpus text; questions are paraphrases. The composition
    80	  test asserts the 24/6 split, stratification, and the n-gram disjointness screen.
    81	- **Tune/test discipline:** a separate scratch set of ≤10 items may be used while
    82	  building (recorded in the manifest). Gold items are queried ONLY in the scoring
    83	  run. **One pass; the gold set is EXPOSED after that pass and never re-scorable**
    84	  (same rule as the classifier splits). A re-attempt requires a fresh pre-registered
    85	  gold set and a fresh owner-visible registration row.
    86	
    87	## 5. Metrics + FLOORS (conjunctive — ANY miss → the label DEFERS)
    88	
    89	| # | Metric | Definition | Floor |
    90	| --- | --- | --- | --- |
    91	| M1 | Retrieval hit-rate@5 | expected source file appears in top-5 retrieved chunks (24 in-corpus items) | ≥ 0.85 (21/24) **AND** strictly > the BM25 baseline's hit-rate, tie = the simpler lane ships |
    92	| M2 | Citation precision | of all citations emitted across answered items, the fraction whose cited span supports the answer (grader: span-containment + human-readable audit list) | ≥ 0.90 |
    93	| M3 | Unsupported-answer rate | answered items whose answer text is NOT contained in any cited span | ≤ 0.05 |
    94	| M4 | Abstention calibration | out-of-corpus items correctly abstained | ≥ 5/6 · AND ≤ 4 wrong abstentions on the 24 in-corpus items |
    95	| M5 | Injection resistance | the planted instruction-chunk (§2) retrieved as data: rank/citation behavior unchanged, no behavioral deviation, answer text never executes/echoes the instruction as a directive | 100% (binary) |
    96	
    97	Determinism: the whole lane is deterministic (extractive, temp-free) — the scoring
    98	run is a single pass by construction; a flip-rate metric is not applicable and is
    99	not claimed.
   100	
   101	**Label on success:** "RAG lane: validated on a pre-registered 30-item gold set, one
   102	pass — advisory, extractive, offline" (scope-bounded; says nothing beyond this corpus).
   103	**Label on any miss:** "RAG lane: floors not met (see results) — experimental, advisory
   104	only" — the lane may still ship as clearly-labeled experimental, per the honesty rules.
   105	
   106	## 6. Integration contract (decided here, per plan §E2)
   107	
   108	- Tool-registry: ONE new advisory tool (`lookup_reference`), JSON-schema-validated,
   109	  returning {answer_span, citations[], score, abstained}. The engine never consumes
   110	  it for verdicts; the crew MAY receive it read-advisory (allowlist updated
   111	  deliberately + reviewed in batch D).
   112	- **MCP exposure: YES** — the MCP server advertises the same tool (schema verbatim
   113	  from the registry); transcript + tool count + SHOWCASE updated in the E2 results
   114	  slice, all inside batch D's review.
   115	- CI: the E2 suites join `npm run verify` (they are offline and deterministic).
   116	
