   700	            <div class="module-body">
   701	              <h3 class="h3">Listings truth check</h3>
   702	              <p class="module-desc">The serving copy vs the system-of-record, line by line &mdash; availability, price, existence, encoding. The committed demo report catches a sold-out item still being served.</p>
   703	            </div>
   704	          </li>
   705	          <li class="module reveal" data-stagger="50">
   706	            <div class="module-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg class="ic" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><use href="#ic-copies"/></svg></div>
   707	            <div class="module-body">
   708	              <h3 class="h3">Protocol conformance</h3>
   709	              <p class="module-desc">Validation against 78 pinned official UCP schemas (spec 2026-04-08) &mdash; and the headline it exists to prove: a feed can be schema-conformant and still false against the merchant&rsquo;s records. Both legs are machine-checked.</p>
   710	            </div>
   711	          </li>
   712	          <li class="module reveal" data-stagger="100">
   713	            <div class="module-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg class="ic" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><use href="#ic-scale"/></svg></div>
   714	            <div class="module-body">
   715	              <h3 class="h3">Fee-cap audit</h3>
   716	              <p class="module-desc">NYC &sect;20-563.3 codified as 17 rules (11 executable predicates + 6 registered non-checkable clauses) over hostile, relabeled statement lines &mdash; with a calibrated classifier in front and the deterministic table deciding.</p>
   717	            </div>
   718	          </li>
   719	        </ol>
   720	      </div>
   721	    </section>
   722	
   723	    <!-- ========================== #evidence ========================== -->
   724	    <section class="station" id="evidence" aria-labelledby="evidence-h2">
   725	      <div class="node" aria-hidden="true"><svg class="ic" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><use href="#ic-spark"/></svg></div>
   726	      <div class="content reveal">
   727	        <p class="eyebrow"><svg class="ic" viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#ic-spark"/></svg> Labels are earned here, or not claimed</p>
   728	        <h2 class="h2" id="evidence-h2">Every quality label traces to a pre-registered run.</h2>
   729	        <p class="prose">The fee-line classifier&rsquo;s first calibration run missed one floor and the label was <em>deferred</em> &mdash; that record stays public. A fresh pre-registered retry then cleared every floor (21/21) and earned it. The live agent-crew run scored 20/20 against floors committed before the run &mdash; and only the two model-directed members carry the &ldquo;agent&rdquo; label, because that is what the pre-registration says the result licenses. The eval evidence dashboard traces every figure to its committed record.</p>
   730	      </div>
   731	    </section>
   732	
   733	    <!-- ========================== #honesty =========================== -->
   734	    <section class="station" id="honesty" aria-labelledby="honesty-h2">
   735	      <div class="node" aria-hidden="true"><svg class="ic" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><use href="#ic-person"/></svg></div>
   736	      <div class="content reveal">
   737	        <p class="eyebrow"><svg class="ic" viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#ic-person"/></svg> What this is &mdash; and what it is not</p>
   738	        <h2 class="h2" id="honesty-h2">A simulated prototype, honest about its own edges.</h2>
   739	        <p class="prose">The restaurant, its menu, and its records are invented; the verification rules, the pinned data-format standard, and the codified fee caps are real. The site is a static replay of committed fixtures &mdash; it initiates nothing. This project began as a merchant activation prototype; that first product is preserved, working, as the legacy activation module.</p>
   740	
   741	        <footer class="foot">
   742	          <span class="foot-status">Simulated prototype, run on demand &mdash; not a live service.</span>
   743	          Every page is a <strong>static replay of committed, labeled fixtures</strong> from a synthetic corpus; this sample <strong>initiates no sends and makes no live calls</strong>. Human-led, AI-assisted, professionally reviewed.
   744	          <strong>Not affiliated with, endorsed by, or connected to</strong> DoorDash, Uber Eats, Grubhub, DataSF, or any named business. Built and directed by Sharan Kumar (github.com/sharanlabs).
   745	        </footer>
   746	      </div>
   747	    </section>
   748	  </main>
   749	
   750	  <p class="site-end">Design-lane sample &mdash; &ldquo;Meridian&rdquo; (S6b, 2026-07-11). Not served by the live site; a design-process record for owner reaction. Brief: docs/design-brief-s6b-2026-07-11.md.</p>
   751	
   752	  <script>
   753	  (function () {
   754	    "use strict";
   755	    var reduceMq = window.matchMedia("(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)");
   756	
   757	    /* --------------------------- hold-to-verify --------------------------- */
   758	    var zone = document.getElementById("hold-zone");
   759	    var btn = document.getElementById("hold-btn");
   760	    var revealPlain = document.getElementById("reveal-plain");
   761	    var details = document.getElementById("verdict-fallback");
   762	    var card = document.getElementById("verdict-card");
   763	    var status = document.getElementById("hold-status");
   764	    var HOLD_MS = 1400;
   765	    var timer = null;
   766	    var holding = false;
   767	    var revealed = false;
   768	
   769	    function setStatus(msg) { if (status) { status.textContent = msg; } }
   770	
   771	    function reveal() {
   772	      if (revealed) { return; }
   773	      revealed = true;
   774	      holding = false;
   775	      if (timer) { clearTimeout(timer); timer = null; }
   776	      zone.classList.remove("holding");
   777	      zone.classList.add("done");
   778	      btn.setAttribute("aria-expanded", "true");
   779	      details.open = true;
   780	      // 320ms ease-out entrance (opacity-only under reduced motion, via CSS)
   781	      requestAnimationFrame(function () { card.classList.add("revealed"); });
   782	      setStatus("Verified against the record. FAIL — 16 findings (11 error, 5 warn). Verdict shown below.");
   783	    }
   784	
   785	    function startHold() {
   786	      if (revealed || holding) { return; }
   787	      // reduced motion: instant state change, no timed fill
   788	      if (reduceMq.matches) { reveal(); return; }
   789	      holding = true;
   790	      zone.classList.add("holding");
   791	      setStatus("Verifying — hold to weigh the serving copy against the record.");
   792	      timer = setTimeout(reveal, HOLD_MS);
   793	    }
   794	
   795	    function cancelHold() {
   796	      if (!holding) { return; }
   797	      holding = false;
   798	      if (timer) { clearTimeout(timer); timer = null; }
   799	      zone.classList.remove("holding");
   800	      setStatus("Released early — the check did not complete. Hold again, or reveal without holding.");
   801	    }
   802	
   803	    // pointer: capture so move/up/cancel resolve to this button
   804	    btn.addEventListener("pointerdown", function (e) {
   805	      if (typeof e.button === "number" && e.button !== 0) { return; }
   806	      try { btn.setPointerCapture(e.pointerId); } catch (err) {}
   807	      e.preventDefault();
   808	      startHold();
   809	    });
   810	    btn.addEventListener("pointerup", function (e) {
   811	      try { btn.releasePointerCapture(e.pointerId); } catch (err) {}
   812	      cancelHold();
   813	    });
   814	    btn.addEventListener("pointercancel", cancelHold);
   815	    btn.addEventListener("pointerleave", cancelHold);
   816	
   817	    // keyboard: Space / Enter — keydown starts, keyup releases, key-repeat guarded
   818	    function isActivateKey(e) {
   819	      return e.key === " " || e.key === "Spacebar" || e.code === "Space" || e.key === "Enter";
   820	    }
   821	    btn.addEventListener("keydown", function (e) {
   822	      if (!isActivateKey(e)) { return; }
   823	      e.preventDefault();            // stop scroll + the native click-activation
   824	      if (e.repeat) { return; }      // guard auto-repeat
   825	      startHold();
   826	    });
   827	    btn.addEventListener("keyup", function (e) {
   828	      if (!isActivateKey(e)) { return; }
   829	      e.preventDefault();
   830	      cancelHold();
   831	    });
   832	    // losing focus mid-hold counts as release
   833	    btn.addEventListener("blur", cancelHold);
   834	
   835	    // no-hold path — completes the same reveal instantly
   836	    revealPlain.addEventListener("click", function () { reveal(); });
   837	
   838	    // JS present: start closed (hold / reveal buttons drive the disclosure;
   839	    // the native <summary> is hidden via the .js CSS rule).
   840	    details.open = false;
   841	
   842	    /* ---------------------- station reveal on scroll ---------------------- */
   843	    var reveals = Array.prototype.slice.call(document.querySelectorAll(".reveal"));
   844	    if ("IntersectionObserver" in window && !reduceMq.matches) {
   845	      var io = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
   846	        entries.forEach(function (entry) {
   847	          if (!entry.isIntersecting) { return; }
   848	          var el = entry.target;
   849	          var delay = parseInt(el.getAttribute("data-stagger") || "0", 10) || 0;
   850	          setTimeout(function () { el.classList.add("in"); }, delay);
   851	          io.unobserve(el);
   852	        });
   853	      }, { threshold: 0.12, rootMargin: "0px 0px -6% 0px" });
   854	      reveals.forEach(function (el) { io.observe(el); });
   855	    } else {
   856	      // no IO or reduced motion: show everything immediately
   857	      reveals.forEach(function (el) { el.classList.add("in"); });
   858	    }
   859	  })();
   860	  </script>
   861	</body>
   862	</html>
