/Users/sharan_98/claude-os/library/_external-skills/emilkowalski-skills/README.md:53:`improve-animations` surveys your whole codebase (not a single diff), audits it across eight categories (purpose & frequency, easing & duration, physicality, interruptibility, performance, accessibility, cohesion, missed opportunities), and presents a prioritized findings table. Pick the ones you want, and it writes self-contained plans into `plans/` — exact files, exact curves, exact durations, plus a feel check — that another agent can execute without any context or taste of its own. It never touches your source code itself.
