docs/plan-multi-agent-execution.md:305:This phase is largely a **swap into seams the A2 orchestrator already exposes** (`recommend?` → Strategist, `draftGenerate?` → Gemini Drafter, `judgeGenerate?` → the reverse judge), plus the new Domain Critic + the LLM Router. The differential, `lib/core/*`, the oracle, the gold sets, and the frozen calibration/trajectory snapshots stay **UNTOUCHED**.
docs/plan-multi-agent-execution.md:309:1. **Strategist/Planner — Groq `gpt-oss-120b` (free).** *Seam:* synthesizes `engagement_state × blocker × root_cause × tenure × risk` into an **approach** — what to emphasize, which objection to pre-empt, tone calibrated to engagement — judgment the deterministic `diagnose().play` (a *routed touch*: channel/template) does not capture. *Anti-theater proof (R-A3-1):* a component eval on a labeled set showing the Strategist's recommendation **diverges from / adds to** `diagnose().play`, not merely restates it. *In:* the deterministic triage + diagnosis (engagement_state, blocker, root_cause_hypothesis, play.touch, tenure, risk) — **no eligibility authority**. *Out:* `Recommendation { route, strategy, tone, rationale }`, where `route` is **advisory** and constrained to the deterministically-allowed envelope (suppressed/ineligible ⇒ may only recommend suppress/hold). RECOMMEND-ONLY.
docs/plan-multi-agent-execution.md:310:2. **Drafter — Gemini Flash (≤ $5, `assertWithinBudget` fail-closed).** *Seam:* generative prose composition (already agentic in spirit). *Cross-family change:* was Groq (`draftOutreachGroq`), now **Gemini** (`lib/agents/draft.ts draftOutreach`, live/mock). *In:* merchant claimable fields **via the `{{MERCHANT}}` injection-cut placeholder** + the Strategist's strategy/tone/angle + **KB §4.2 prevention rules** (R-A3-5) + (on re-draft) the Router's revision instruction. *Out:* `OutreachDraft` (subject/body/claims[]); the injection-cut + post-gen `MISSING_PLACEHOLDER`/`NAME_LEAK`/`UNRESOLVED_PLACEHOLDER` validation carry over.
docs/plan-multi-agent-execution.md:311:3. **Domain Critic — Groq `gpt-oss-120b` (cross-family vs the Gemini Drafter).** *Seam:* the calibrated **Effective**-axis evaluative judgment (B1/B2 `lib/agents/domain-judge.ts`); introduces SC-2 into the loop. **ADVISORY** — never gates eligibility/send (locked in B2; the advisory-invariant red-green test stays). *In:* the draft + the merchant **situation** (engagement_state, blocker) — **withholds `diagnose().play`** (R-DARCH-2 no-answer-leakage). *Out:* `DomainJudgeResult` (3 per-dim verdicts: matched-to-blocker · engagement-appropriate · no-over-promise + overall `domain_defective` + rationale). **Independent:** formed WITHOUT the faithfulness verdict as input.
docs/plan-multi-agent-execution.md:312:4. **Router/Conductor — Groq `gpt-oss-120b`.** *Seam (THE anti-theater crux the owner accepted):* reads **both** critics' verdicts (faithfulness failures [gating] + domain dimensions [advisory]) and forms a **prioritized, concrete revision strategy** — which fix first, how to reconcile a faithfulness-fail against a domain-weak signal, whether the issue is redraft-fixable vs hold-for-human-with-reason — plus the final **route recommendation** + the human-facing rationale. This is real synthesis the deterministic `buildReflection` (single-failure string assembly) does not do. *Anti-theater proof (R-A3-1):* a component eval on **multi-failure** cases where the LLM Router produces a more targeted revision than `buildReflection`; **RECOMMEND-ONLY** — the send transition stays the deterministic `simulate_send` + `assertEligibilityUntouched` (R-A3-3). *Fallback (honest):* if the Router cannot beat `buildReflection`, it is demoted to the deterministic conductor and the count claim drops to "3 agents + a conductor."
docs/plan-multi-agent-execution.md:316:- **Drafter → critics:** the `OutreachDraft` goes to BOTH the Faithfulness check (forward gatekeeper tool + reverse Groq judge) AND the Domain Critic — **in parallel, independent**.
docs/plan-multi-agent-execution.md:325:- **R-A3-2 (Ubiquitous — cross-family restored):** The Drafter SHALL be Gemini Flash; **both** the reverse-faithfulness judge **and** the Domain Critic SHALL be Groq `gpt-oss-120b` — maker≠judge at the **model** layer (`R-ARCH-3` restored, the independence A2 deferred under R-LOOP-5).
docs/plan-multi-agent-execution.md:330:- **R-A3-7 (Event-driven — Gemini live = consequential paid pick):** WHEN the Drafter is run live, the system SHALL gate it on **owner sign-off + a live date-anchored Gemini model-id/pricing freshness check (`RULES.md` §6) + a Codex cross-check**, SHALL respect the $5 cap (sized as demo-set × `maxIterations` × Flash price — the Drafter runs **every re-draft**), and SHALL ship offline machinery (mock/DI, $0) FIRST. "Any live spend" is an owner-gated stop independent of the $5 cap.
docs/plan-multi-agent-execution.md:331:- **R-A3-8 (Ubiquitous — directional label held):** A3 SHALL NOT upgrade the judges' "calibrated — directional, pending the ~100 floor" label on the basis of running inside the multi-agent loop. The Domain Critic + faithfulness judge were calibrated over the **synthetic gold set**, not over live **Gemini** prose (a new draft distribution) — note this in `docs/domain-calibration-status.md` + `docs/judge-calibration-status.md`.
docs/plan-multi-agent-execution.md:332:- **R-A3-9 (Event-driven — K re-set for A3):** WHEN the A3 live self-correction milestone runs, the floor **K** SHALL be re-pinned on a fresh held-out split (the stronger Gemini drafter changes the error distribution); value recorded at the A3 live gate, **never** tuned on the test split.
